{
  "texts": [
    "in [227] proposed an E2E predictive beamforming scheme.",
    "In particular, they trained an attention-based long short-term memory network to extract the temporal features and learn the mapping from the echo signal to the beamforming matrix, obtaining higher communication rate than the two-stage DL-based algorithm.",
    "Zhang et al. [228] proposed a transmission protocol to establish the direct relationship from the echo signal to the beamforming vector, bypassing the need for CSI acquisition and reducing the overhead.",
    "According to the echo signal, they optimized the transmit beamforming to maximize the sum achievable rate, and proposed a convolution transformer network to further handle it.",
    "Their proposed network leveraged both the convolutional module and attention mechanism to extract local and global dependencies for the performance enhancement."
  ]
}